review_blob: Overrated. Not my favorite of the Dogfish line, nor in my top ten of all time.
My favorite from the Dogfish series. Great flavor, balanced between hops & barley, with a little citrus flavor and definite sweetness.
Very strong flavor, almost makes you wonder where a beer ends and something else starts. No hoppiness in the flavor, though, strangely enough. Color is copper, head is weak and a pale orange as well.
Bottle. Nice color and appearance, although the head was a little soft for my tastes. The flavor was annoyingly missing - it reminded me most strongly of Coors.

Bottle. Similar to 60-minute IPA, with nice coppery color & thick white head. Very flavorful - hoppy and malty - and great aroma. Despite strong flavors, easy to drink both room temperature and chilled. Simply my favorite beer.
Bottle. Nice coppery color & thick blonde head. Very flavorful - hoppy and malty - and great aroma. Despite strong flavors, easy to drink both room temperature and chilled.
Bottle. Interesting cork top. Light amber color, thin head that cleared away quickly. Not too bubbly. Strong sweet apple aroma and flavor; I felt I was drinking a cider rather than a beer.

Bottle. Looks like a stout, except for the small head. Good drinking beer. Dark brown color and malty flavor, with a hint of chocolate and walnut. Light and thin, although you would expect more given the appearance of a stout.
Bottle. Fruity and hoppy, with crisp aftertaste and distinct aroma. Strong sense of berries and plums; small but creamy head.
Bottle. initial flavor rich, but indistinct tones. Aftertaste clean and crisp, but smoky.
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

review_blob: Oilcan. If you like a smooth rich bitter, this is the one for you. Not as hoppy as most bitters, and richer in flavors than most as well, this serves as a good pre-dinner beer.
Bottle. A good beer if it is ice cold and the heat is getting to you. Dont go to it if youre looking for flavor or something exciting.
